\subsection{Social media analysis}
As a complex information ecosystem, social media in social media analysis can be deconstructed into 4 core elements:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Content:} This primarily refers to user-generated posts, comments, images, videos, and various interaction data (e.g., like counts, retweets). Content is the smallest component of social media. As the direct carrier of semantics, it is the raw expression of emotions, stances, and facts.以及等等？
    \item \textbf{User:} As the generator of content，user 还作为信息传播节点而存在于social media中. 我们关注user的 individual attributes such as profiles, historical posting records, and position within the network such as follower count, interaction patterns。 These elements collectively 表达者user的社会特征
    \item \textbf{Network:} Social network is a concept concerning the hierarchy of information dissemination. As a data structure of graph, it generally treats users as nodes and interactions (follows, retweets, comments) as edges. Network reveals the pathways of information dissemination, the clustering patterns of communities, and the diffusion process of influence from individuals to groups.
